Paas -- Platform as a service:
-------------------------------------
Azure SQL Database (DBaas). create a database resource and use it as a service.
Every thing is taken care by Microsoft.
Additional feature -- Built in high availability, Intelligense.
Pay as you go
scale up or scale out without any interuption.
Multiple deployment models

Choose right service tier
Test the high availability and DR
Azure has inbuilt performance report monitering
Change control is you responsibilty
Security tools are present to moniter
Builtin backup, recovery and patches
Builtin advanced intelligense and security

PAAS has 3 different types of deployment options

1. Single database:
single isolated database which is perfect for application having single database as a source.
Has it own guaranted compute power, Memory and storage

2. Elastic pool
Collection of single databases with a shared set of resources such as CPU and memoy. Resources are shared equally among the databases.

3. Managed Instance(Most recent)
Aset of databases that can be used together, easy migration of on-premises databases.
Dedicated instance of SQL server in your virtual network
Each managed instance has its guaranteed resources which are shared by the managed instance databases equally.




